{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase Maternity/Shared Parental pay in line with National Living Wage",
        "additional_details": "Assuming a working week is 38 hours, \u00a3151.97 per week is \u00a34 per hour, significantly lower than the National Living Wage of \u00a38.91/hr.\r\n \r\nWe would like Government to raise Statutory Maternity and Shared Parental Pay so that from week 7 this at least matches the National Living Wage at 38/hrs a week:\r\n \r\nWe would like the Government to:\r\n \r\n- Continue the first 6 weeks of pay at 90% average earnings\r\n- Amend the following 33 weeks of SMP/ShPP to be \u00a3338.51 per week or 90% average earnings (whichever is lower), to reflect National Living Wage of \u00a38.91 at 38 hours week\r\n \r\nEmployers could continue to offer enhanced pay as desired.",
        "background": "Currently Statutory Maternity and Shared Parental Pay (correct as at April 2021) is 90% of weekly wages for 39 weeks, capped at \u00a3151.97 per week from week 7.",
